x4freetext: Appendix
Evaluation.
This evaluation of U-237 inelastic scattering
excitation cross-section is a necessary step in an
evaluation of the energy distribution of the
secondary neutrons from the U-238(n,2n)U-237 and
U-238(n,3n)U-236 reactions.  See VIEN-V0004.
Optical model and statistical theory calculations were
made with the ABACUS-NEARREX code, by
- E.H.Auerbach, ABACUS-2 program operation and input
description, BNL-6562 (1962), and
- P.A.Moldauer,C.A.Engelbrecht,G.J.Duffy, NEARREX,
A computer code for nuclear reaction calculations,
1)Optical model parameters from the author`s Pu-241
evaluation, Caner, Yiftah, IA-1276 (1973).
2)U-237 energy level scheme was constructed from
table of isotopes and others and summarized in
Table III of Nucl.Sci.Eng.,59(1976)395.
3)Recommended fission cross-section is based on data
by Macnally et al.,Phys.Rev.,C9(1964)717.
4)Observed level spacing (=3.5 ev) and capture width
(=35 milli-eV) were taken from Macnally et al.,
So far the only available evaluation of U-237 is that
of B.Hinkelmann (Mrs.Schatz), KFK-1186 (1970).
However it does not contain information on the
inelastic scattering cross-section.
Approved by M.Caner, 1977/03/08.
